{
  "texts": [
    "Self-efficacy surveys are also prominent in two studies (e.g., Geng et al. 2019; Lin et al. 2024), emphasizing their importance in assessing teachers' confidence in STEM disciplines.",
    "Several studies combine different data sources to enrich findings; for example, Huang et al. (2022) Objectives Foci in Professional Development.",
    "These studies predominantly aim to enhance pedagogical skills in STEM education, focusing on methodologies that can be directly applied in classroom settings.",
    "Many studies, such as Stonier and Adarkwah (2023) and Ong et al. (2020), have focused on developing teachers' pedagogical skills, particularly in STEM education.",
    "This includes improving teachers' abilities to integrate STEM subjects effectively into their teaching practices."
  ]
}